President Biden visited Osan Air Base in Pyeongtaek, Republic of Korea, where he expressed gratitude and appreciation to the American and Korean troops stationed there. He highlighted the importance of the U.S.-ROK alliance and the shared sacrifice that formed it during the Korean War. Biden emphasized the significance of deterring threats and underwriting stability, not just for the Korean Peninsula but for the world. He acknowledged the strong bond between the American and Korean forces and thanked them for their service in defending their countries. President Yoon of the Republic of Korea also expressed gratitude for the U.S. troops and emphasized the friendship and strength of the ROK-U.S. alliance. He praised the role of Osan Air Base in responding to the increasing nuclear and missile threat from North Korea and highlighted the importance of defending the security of the Korean Peninsula. Overall, both leaders expressed their appreciation and support for the troops stationed at Osan Air Base and their commitment to the alliance between the U.S. and the Republic of Korea.